data.name: Super Rod
rules: You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).
Shuffle 3 in any combination of Pokémon and basic Energy cards from your discard pile back into your deck.

data.name: First Ticket
rules: You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

"Before you flip a coin to decide who goes first in a game, you may play this card. Dont flip that coin, and you go first. If both players play First Ticket, flip the coin as normal. (You may play only 1 First Ticket before you flip that coin.)"

data.name: EXP.ALL
rules: "Attach EXP. ALL to 1 of your Pokémon (excluding Pokémon-ex and Pokémon that has an owner in its name) that doesnt already have a Pokémon Tool attached to it. If that Pokémon is Knocked Out, discard this card.", "During your opponents turn, if 1 of your Active Pokémon is Knocked Out by your opponents attack, you may take 1 basic Energy card attached to that Knocked Out Pokémon and attach it to the Pokémon with EXP.ALL attached to it. If you do, discard EXP.ALL."
